  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff date in October 2023, sorting through calendar apps for iOS with the specific feature of crossing off events as you go through the day can be a bit tricky since many apps focus more on scheduling and reminders rather than physically crossing off items. However, here are a few options that might meet your needs:\n\n1. **Fantastical**: This is one of the most popular calendar apps for iOS with a feature-rich environment. While it doesn't specifically allow you to cross off events, it offers comprehensive scheduling tools and integrates with reminders, allowing you to mark tasks as completed.\n\n2. **Google Calendar**: While Google Calendar does not feature cross-off capabilities directly within the calendar for events, you can integrate it with Google Tasks which allows you to mark tasks as completed. This combination can provide a similar functionality.\n\n3. **Microsoft Outlook**: Outlook's mobile app combines email and calendar features efficiently. Tasks can be marked as complete, though technically this is within the task management part rather than crossing off events on the calendar.\n\n4. **Agenda**: Though primarily used for note-taking, Agenda integrates calendar events with notes, allowing you to create tasks and mark them as complete.\n\n5. **Any.do**: Any.do integrates tasks and calendar events very well, giving you a unified platform where you can cross off tasks as you complete them, and it syncs well with your calendar.\n\nThese apps offer some form of task management that can scratch the itch of crossing off events throughout your day. Be sure to experiment with these apps to find the best fit for your workflow.",
